<h2 id="biodiversity-time-travels-the-use-of-historical-plant-genomes-in-biodiversity-research">Biodiversity time travels: The use of historical plant genomes in biodiversity research</h2>

<p>Our first seminar series was part of a series in Molecular identification of plants for science and society. 
Very proud to have organized and chaired this seminar. What is common in this seminar? the use of aDNA from collections to solve evolutionary questions. 
The subjects ranged from a restrospective on plant genetic diversity using ancient DNA, invasive species,</p>

